          <h4>Registration process</h4>
          <hr>
          <p>All information related to dates and times stated below is based on GMT+7 time zone (local time in Thailand). Please note that the process will be done through our <a href="https://www.simpicofficial.org" target="_blank">official website</a></p>
          <p>Upon the account registration, you will receive the username and password, which will be used throughout the application process.</p>
          <br/>

          <h4>The competition date</h4>
          <hr>
          <p>The SIMPICSED will be held during 12-14 MARCH 2021.</p>
          <br/>

          <h4>Competition Criteria</h4>
          <hr/>
          <p>Only medical students, either in preclinical or clinical years, are eligible to apply for the competition.</p>
          <p>Thai medical schools: Each medical school can apply a maximum of 3 representative teams, 1 team for online competition and 2 teams for on-site competition. The representative teams Each team must consist of 4 medical students, and (optional) 1 advisor.</p>
          <p>International medical schools: Each medical school can apply a maximum of 3 representative teams. Due to COVID-19, All of the representative teams are required to compete in the online competition. However, if the COVID-19 situation is alleviated and the representatives accept all the quarantine conditions and government issues, you may request a change to on-site competition within Jan 3, 2021. Each representative team must consist of 4 medical students, and (optional) 1 advisor.</p>
          <p>Notably, as an official partner with IFMSA-Thailand, IFMSA members from any NMO will be given special quotas to attend the competition. Due to COVID-19, All of the representative teams are required to compete in the online competition. However, if the COVID-19 situation is alleviated and the representatives accept all the quarantine conditions and government issues, you may request a change to on-site competition within Jan 3, 2021. Each NMO can send a maximum of 3 representative teams, consisting of 4 medical students from any medical school from the NMO region.</p>
          <p>*The substitution of candidates after registration is not permitted without necessity.</p>
          <br/>

          <h4>On-site competition</h4>
          <hr/>
          <br/>

          <h6><b>Registration Timeline</b></h6>
          <p>Early period : Nov 8 - Nov 21, 2020 Registration fee 9600 THB (approximately 300 USD)</p>
          <p>Regular period : Nov 22 - Dec 19, 2020 Registration fee 10080 THB  (approximately 315 USD)</p>
          <p>Announcement of qualified teams : Jan 3, 2021</p>
          <p>Payment period and extra information : Jan 4 - Jan 22, 2021</p>
          <p>Payment must be made via PayPal or International transfer within the payment period. (Payment confirmation in the official website within 10 days upon the proof of payment submission.)</p>
          <p>Extra information submission: you will be required to fill in the extra information within the same period as payment.</p>
          <p>Official announcement of competitor list: Jan 24, 2021</p>
          <p>* Due to our limited seat, qualified applicants will be selected based on the motivation letter and the short essay submitted.</p>

          <h6><b>Registration fee</b> covers the following expenses</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Academic competition, workshop and parties</li>
            <li>Transportation between the hotel and the competition venue is provided daily at the scheduled time.</li>
            <li>Meals and snack breaks during the competition and two special parties, welcome and farewell parties.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>* Registration fee excludes the flight tickets and transportation neither leaving nor arriving at the airport. Importantly, we recommend you to book a return flight on Mar 15, 2021.</p>
          <br/>

