          <h6><b>Regulation for COVID-19 situation</b></h6>
          <p>Here are our plans if there is the 2nd wave of COVID-19 during the registration period.</p>
          <ol>
            <li>If the COVID-19 outbreak in Thailand is controlled, the competition will be held as a hybrid with a maximum of 40 teams for on-site competition welcoming up to 10 of International travelable teams.</li>
            * This decision will be announced within Jan 3, 2021
            <li>If there is the second-wave in January to March or an outbreak in Siriraj hospital, all competition will shift to online competition. The paid-team will be refunded the difference. </li>
            * The decision is when the government announced not to hold such a meeting or conference.
          </ol>
          <br/>

          <h6><b>On-site regulation</b></h6>
          <p>Due to the COVID-19 situation, our team concerns a lot about our delegates' safety. Here are our regulations for COVID-19 situations in the on-site SIMPICSED.</p>
          <ol>
            <li>Keep social distancing</li>
            We limited the participant teams which will be social distancing enough in the auditory hall.
            <li>Wear face mask</li>
            We offer a face mask for every delegate in our event, in order to limit the spread of certain respiratory diseases, including SARS-CoV-2.
            <li>Use alcohol gel</li>
            For your hygiene, there will be alcohol gel everywhere in SIMPICSED.
            <li>Cleaning routine</li>
            We keep hygiene for all our stuffs in SIMPIC regularly.

          </ol>

